---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import ArchitectureSidebar from "../../components/ArchitectureSidebar.astro";

// The Architecture section landing / Overview (site-shell restructure). The
// section gathers the philosophy (The Four Pillars) and points out to the two
// host-routed surfaces where the specifics live — Decisions (adrs.) and Standards
// (standards.). The full architecture reference (the shells/services/domains
// decomposition) is not yet published; this Overview is honest about that and
// becomes an Astro content collection per launch-artifacts §3 when it lands.
//
// On-demand (not prerendered) so the host-routing middleware runs for it (issue
// #2): a prerendered page is served from the static-assets layer before
// middleware and would leak onto the adrs./standards. subdomains as a 200. As an
// on-demand route it 404s on those hosts and only resolves on the apex.
export const prerender = false;

// Edge-cacheable like the other section stubs so dropping prerender does not turn
// a stable page into an uncached origin hit.
Astro.response.headers.set("Cache-Control", "public, max-age=60, s-maxage=300");
---

<Base
  title="Architecture — rsb.sh"
  description="How the RSB ecosystem is built: the four pillars every decision is tested against, the decisions themselves, and the standards they imply."
>
  <ArchitectureSidebar slot="sidebar" />

  <article class="architecture">
    <h1>Architecture</h1>

    <p>
      This is where the RSB ecosystem explains how it is built. It rests on
      <a href="/architecture/pillars">the four pillars</a> every decision is tested
      against; the decisions themselves are recorded as ADRs at
      <a href="https://adrs.rsb.sh">adrs.rsb.sh</a>, and the rules those decisions
      imply are written down as standards at
      <a href="https://standards.rsb.sh">standards.rsb.sh</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      The full architecture reference — the shells, services, and domains the
      applications are built from — is still being written. For now this section
      holds the pillars and points you to the decisions and standards. It will grow
      as the work does.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .architecture {
    color: var(--color-neutral-700);
  }

  .architecture h1 {
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    line-height: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--color-neutral-900);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .architecture p {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .architecture a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-neutral-400);
  }

  .architecture a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-neutral-900);
  }
</style>
